      #Analyzing Numerical 
      k = len(shopping_mall[numerical].columns)
      n = 3
      m = (k - 1) // n + 1 
      fig, axes = plt.subplots(m, n, figsize=(n * 6, m * 4))
      for i, (name, col) in enumerate(shopping_mall[numerical].iteritems()):
          r, c = i // n, i % n
          ax = axes[r, c]
          col.hist(ax=ax)
          ax2 = col.plot.kde(ax=ax, secondary_y=True, title=name)
          ax2.set_ylim(0)

      #Analyzing Categorical Variable
      ​
      fig, ax = plt.subplots(3, 1, figsize=(20, 15))
      for variable, subplot in zip(categorical, ax.flatten()):
          df_2 = shopping_mall[[variable,'revenue']].groupby(variable).revenue.sum().reset_index()
          df_2.columns = [variable,'total_revenue']
          sns.barplot(x=variable, y='total_revenue', data=df_2 , ax=subplot)
          for label in subplot.get_xticklabels():
              label.set_rotation(90)
